Title: Ask a Startup Investor: Online AMA (Ask Me Anything)
Description:
Ask a Startup Investor: Online AMA (Ask Me Anything)

Zoom Link for anyone that registered last minute and didn't get the zoom link: https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83412524308?pwd=Y3NLSWxtbFh1RU1qMmRNL25iblorUT09

Meeting ID: 834 1252 4308
Passcode: 974572

Event Registration Link: https://fi.co/e/298865 (Please ensure that you register as soon as possible to receive the zoom link - to avoid any last minute problems of not having the zoom link.

If you are currently raising funding for your startup, or are looking to raise funding in the future, then join this online 'Ask me Anything' (AMA) event featuring some of South Asia's top startup venture funds and angel investors that are interested in Sri Lankan startups. 

Learn how startup funding works, how investors evaluate pitches, the types of founders investors are looking for, and more. Anyone interested in raising funding from Sri Lanka or South Asia angel investors or venture capitalists are welcome to attend. Come with your questions, our investors will be ready to answer them! 

Investor Panel
Ashok Verma
Founding Partner/CEO at nVentures which invests and empowers early stage startups in South Asia. Ashok co-founded nCinga Innovations (a Sri Lankan startup) in 2014, a digital Transformation SaaS Startup focused on the garment industry. Ashok helped raise investments for the company, which was acquired by Zilingo (Singapore) in Dec 2019. Ashok has 25+ years of experience in leadership roles at tech MNCs like Cisco/HPE and driving Sales/Business Development in the APAC region.

Anjali Malhotra
Angel Investor, Startup Mentor, and CXO turned consultant, Anjali is the Founder/CEO of Take3Lab, a venture studio based in India. She is the Director of Founder Institute Delhi (India) and an Advisor for Loyal VC (Canada), a leading investor in Founder Institute graduates around the world.  She is the Founder of C-Xcel and has 30 years of experience in strategy and business including Chief Customer/Marketing Officer for Aviva India and Executive VP Marketing for DishTV. 

Afshin Moayed
Partner at Razor Capital, Afshin finds and backs exceptional entrepreneurs solving important problems in Bangladesh and South Asia.  Previously he was Co-Founder & CEO of Individuum. Exposed to both sides of the table, he is Interested in solving problems that matter for the individual and society whilst creating abundance for all stakeholders. He recently joined the board of Ireco Trading & Production S.A., a leading nut supplier in Europe.

Kavi Raj Joshi
Founder & Managing Director of Next Venture Corp. He is an entrepreneur, early stage investor and startup ecosystem builder in Nepal. He has Founded and managed multiple startup incubation programs, a business accelerator and investors network in Nepal. He has been on a mission to make entrepreneurship accessible to more people. 

Who Should Attend?
  • Anyone who is thinking about raising money for their startup 
  • Anyone that wants an understanding of how investors evaluate startups/businesses
  • Anyone interested in startups in South Asi

Title: FI Event: Meet Accelerators, Investors & More in Sri Lanka & South Asia
Description:
Zoom Link to join event: 
https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88087708163?pwd=NWVjVGQ1dkxLZlA4eXBGRHpVUWlSZz09

Startup organizations you can meet and learn about:

  1. Founder Institute South Asia regional program (Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, & Maldives will be present today)
  2. Lankan Angel Network
  3. John Keells X
  4. Accelerating Asia
  5. Seedstars
  6. BetterStories (Bangladesh)
  7. Women's Entrepreneurs Organization
  8. Intellea Partnership

Event Description & Registration link:

Meet the South Asia Startup Ecosystem: Accelerators, Investors & More (fi.co)
 

Meet the South Asia Startup Ecosystem: Accelerators, Investors & More

This event will focus on opportunities for startups based in Bangladesh, Maldives and Sri Lanka. South Asia has a fast growing startup ecosystem, and entrepreneurs have many resources and funding available to help them in their journey. However, many people don't know about all of the resources or funding available, the differences between them, or what resources or funding are right for them. At this online and interactive event, we will gather representatives from different entrepreneurial and investment organizations to outline the local resources, funding options, and provide tips on how to build or grow a startup in South Asia.

Reminder we are not cancelling the event due to the power cut today.

Title: Meet Startup Investors: FI SL Online Free Event
Description:
Meet Startup Investors Online 

Register here: https://fi.co/e/240872

Finding investment is hard. Learn the best methods to secure funding for your startup or business featuring some of Sri Lanka's top startup investors and related organizations. Learn how startup funding works, how investors evaluate pitches, the types of founders investors are looking for, and more. Come with your questions, our investors will be ready to answer them! We will also be answering questions regarding FI's Equity Collective and FI Funding Lab.

Panel Details

  • Chalinda Abeykoon, CEO, Lankan Angel Network  
  • Love Yadav, General Partner, Lion Ventures  
  • Nilendra Weerasinghe, Chief Corporate Advisory Officer, NDB Investment Bank Limited  
  • Sarinda Unamboowe, CEO/Managing Director,MAS Kreeda 
  • Mangala Karunaratne, Founder & CEO, Calcey Technologies
  • AyamiWanasinghe, Managing Director, Founder Institute Sri Lanka

Who Should Attend?

  • Anyone interested in startups, investing or accelerators  
  • Anyone who is thinking about raising money for their startup or business 
  • Anyone that wants an understanding of how investors evaluate businesses 
  • Anyone that wants to learn how to find the right investors including the best ways to approach and build relationships with investors 

Webinar Join Link: https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84808933939?pwd=RU5WTVhTQVorSSt3UCtTVVVpa3J1QT09

This webinar is hosted by the Founder Institute, the worldâs largest pre-seed accelerator. We help you build a business that matters through constant feedback from global startup experts, and a structured process that increases focus and reduces time and cost. Since 2009, over 5,000 companies have used the Founder Institute to build global businesses, solve big problems, raise funding, building a co-founding team, recruit a team, transition from employee to entrepreneur, and more.

You can learn about the Sri Lanka program on our website, or apply or enroll to the program here.

Or if you would like to attend more startup events, visit http://fi.co/events/colombo.

Title: Pie & AI: SLAAI - Colombo Artificial Intelligence Meetup (Thursday, 27th January 2022, 5:00 PM to 6:00 PM (GMT/UTC +5:30))
Description:
Pie & AI: SLAAI - Colombo Artificial Intelligence Meetup (Thursday, 27th January 2022, 5:00 PM to 6:00 PM (GMT/UTC +5:30))

"Bayesian RNN and Physics Informed Neural Network 101" by Prof. Jose Manuel Ramirez (Assistant Professor at Yachay Tech University, Ecuador)

(1.) Online Event Link:
Join Zoom Meeting: https://learn.zoom.us/j/64124495918?pwd=dW40a3VOcFBFTUxrdGkzMHFHOGxtZz09

Meeting ID: 641 2449 5918
Passcode: bt6i*Lih

(2.) Content:
In this presentation, Prof. Jose will present a really simple scheme to set and run a Bayesian RNN, with the idea of estimating parameters after optimization and being scalable to more sophisticated cells like LSTM or GRUs. Aso Prof. Jose has been following (in the literature) a way to train Neural Networks that follow physic laws in the form of differential equations.

Here is the Bayesian Material: https://github.com/josemramirez/pie-ai-jan22

(3.) Speaker:
Jose Manuel was born in Caracas Venezuela. He obtained his undergraduate Physics degree at the University of Carabobo (Venezuela) in 2000 (first of class). Then he attended a PhD program created between the Instituto Venezolano de Investigaciones CientÃ­ficas (IVIC) and the High Energy Laboratory of the NASAâs Goddard Space Flight Center in Maryland EEUU, with mentoring of Timothy Kalman and Claudio Mendozaâs group. Then earned a fellow in Germany (2006-2008) to work on X-ray Astronomy at the Max Planck Institute for Extraterrestrial Physics, and later at the Astrophysics Institute of Potsdam (2008-2011) to collaborate in the XMM Newtonâs operational centre of the European Space Agency (ESA).

He went back to Venezuela in 2012 to lead the Computational Physics laboratory at IVIC (reaching the level of Associate Researcher III) until 2017, where he has been actively collaborating with scientific groups around the world like EEUU, Germany, Mexico (CINVESTAV) and Ecuador.

Profile pages:
https://www.yachaytech.edu.ec/perfil/jose-manuel-ramirez-ph-d/?source=academy
https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=25028510100

Title: Invitation: Startup Idea/Elevator Pitch Online Event - Sri Lanka & South Asia
Description:
Zoom link: https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86037283334?pwd=SnUxQ0FsMlMxL2h0eDg1d0t1UUdyQT09
 
Event Title: Startup Idea/Elevator Pitch Online Event - Sri Lanka & South Asia
 
Do you have a startup, or a strong idea for a startup? Could you use blunt, honest feedback on your elevator pitch or startup idea? On this live and interactive online event you can pitch your ideas to a panel of startup founders, investors, and experts for feedback, all from the comfort of your home. Even if you don't want to pitch, you are invited to hear startup ideas and watch how the experts analyze businesses or startup ideas. Submitting an elevator pitch or startup idea is optional. To submit your elevator pitch (1-2 sentence), visit https://forms.gle/oY3hX3HQJvTy5bhr9

Neeraj Saxena: Managing Partner at Xscale & Univision Fund. We Invest in and scale B2B SaaS and Deep-Tech Startups. Previously lead Global Strategy & Go-to-Market for $1 Billion B2B SaaS Business.

Nio Liyanage: Formerly at Apple with deep experience in Venture Capital and Strategy Consulting. He personally holds equity in 15+ ventures, has advised 250+ startups, built 15+ accelerator programs, founded 4 companies, sits on several boards, and is a Venture Partner for multiple funds.

Fathhi Mohamed - Co-founder of DishServe (Indonesia/Sri Lanka), PickMe (Sri Lanka's leading startup - similar to Uber) and Yoho that have raised over USD 10 million.

Ayesha Ratnayake - Co-founder of Show & Tell, which helps startups make great first impressions with engaging presentations. She also raised USD 500,000 for Affno Ventures.

Yaamin Mohamed - Co-founder of Spark Hub Maldives, Co-Director of Startup Grind X, and Lead Organizer of Techstars Startup Weekend Maldives and Lean Startup Machine Maldives.

Submitting a pitch is optional. To submit your elevator pitch (1-2 sentence), visit https://forms.gle/oY3hX3HQJvTy5bhr9

Who should Attend?
  • Anyone interested in getting feedback and/or seeing others get feedback on their startup ideas or elevator pitches from a panel of experts.
  • Anyone who wants feedback from leading startup entrepreneurs and experts
  • Anyone that wants feedback on their startup idea
  • Anyone who has an early-stage or later stage startup and wants expert feedback on making a good first impression elevator pitch
  • Anyone who has an idea for a startup or a tech company
  • Anyone who needs practice and expert advice on pitching
Who Pitches?
We will be selecting people from the audience to pitch, and will do as many as time allows. To prepare, work on your one sentence pitch at http://fi.co/madlibs. To submit your startup idea / elevator pitch (1-2 sentence), visit https://forms.gle/oY3hX3HQJvTy5bhr9

Spectators are welcome!
Even if you don't want to pitch, you are invited to register, hear startup ideas, and watch how the experts analyze and critique new businesses. If you are looking for more information on pitching your startup, see this Startup Pitch Deck Guide or download startup pitch templates.

Title: Invitation: Learn how to build a tech startup that customers love with Hiraash (CTO, Multiplier - Raised $60M)
Description:
Zoom Link: https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83315101284?pwd=Vng3QjVGdXN6Tkd4NC95THpwbUpBdz09
 
Register here to receive Zoom link: https://fi.co/event/ama-with-hiraash-thawfeek-cto-multiplier-raised-60m-in-sri-lanka-sri-lanka-south-asia-2022.
 
Learn how to build or grow a tech startup that customers love. Hiraash Thawfeek (CTO, Multiplier and Co-founder, Creately) will share how he got started and what he has learnt over the years. Best way to succeed is to learn from a mentor who has successfully done it before. Multiplier recently raised $60 million in a funding round co-led by Tiger Global and Sequoia Capital India. Creately is one of Sri Lanka's most successful tech startups.
 
We are very lucky to have Hiraash talk at this event for us. Given the current situation in Sri Lanka, a lot of people are struggling to figure out how to survive. It is possible to start a tech startup with limited resources and no investment. Creately was entirely bootstrapped by the founders with no external investment and is one of the most successful tech startups to emerge from Sri Lanka. 
 
Please share this with anyone that may be interested in this event. Please feel free to share the email or invite them using this calendar invite.
